# No dash separators in UI copy

Do not use short hyphens (` - `), en dashes (` – `), or em dashes (` — `) as clause separators in customer-facing or admin-facing copy. They make the site look like generic AI writing.

Prefer full stops, commas, or short separate sentences.

Bad: `Official buy rate — lock today’s rate…`
Good: `Official buy rate. Lock today’s rate…`

Also avoid decorative separators like middle dots (` · `) in marketing lines when a period works.

Keep hyphens only where English requires them in real compound words (e.g. `real-time` if already used), in code, URLs, CSS, and math/minus signs. Never use a dash as a stylish pause between clauses.
